    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a meticulously preserved 2003 BMW M3 (E46) in Carbon Black. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system recently calibrated for optimal overlap. This specimen features a crisp 6-speed Getrag manual transmission paired with a torque-sensing limited-slip differential. The chassis integrity is superlative, with proactive subframe reinforcement and a refreshed suspension featuring Bilstein dampers and polyurethane bushings for precise toe and camber retention. Engine health is verified via recent Blackstone oil analysis, and the rod bearings have been replaced with high-performance treated shells. This is a turn-key, collector-grade example with zero mechanical parasitic loss and a flawless factory finish.",
